Template Name: Add Auckland Council IFO - Foundation Checklist (Version 3)

name: Clearly identify area/element covered in this inspection
If the identified area/element is the last partial inspection relating to this inspection type, please complete this inspection as a FULL INSPECTION
Is this a partial inspection or a full inspection
Detailed breakdown of element(s) including location and grid references relating to this inspection
Attach marked up plan detailing element(s), location and grid references relating to this inspection
Does the work being undertaken comply with the issued building consent or approved minor variations or amendments
Latest building consent number (consider any minor variation(s)/amendment(s))
Attach all relevant drawings with revision numbers clearly detailed
If "NO" what are the discrepancies? (comment below and attach evidence of discrepencies)
Is this inspection the outcome of a previous failed inspection
If "Yes" detail when the previous failed inspection occurred (date) and reason for failed result
Does the installation of this building element compromise any previously inspected building elements?
Select "NO" if this has been considered & does not compromise any previously inspected building elements (attach any relevant supporting evidence below)
If "YES" explain below (what is compromised, how it it is compromised & how this will be mitigated/managed)
Building footprint shape and size set out as per plan
Check building set out as per plan. Check footprint layout dimensions and shape against plans.
Surveyor to certify siting/setout - pass once relevant documentation is attached and below items checked
Finished floor level as per plan
Check finished floor level using datum on site plan.
Check ground contours and datum's heights match plans.
Boundary flagged and string lined. Check  minimum 3 boundary pegs. Measure boundary to building outline as per plan
Reason to pass as follows (if applicable): To protect environment by controlling erosion/surface water run off/ silt contaminating council drains, waterways.
Select appropriate exposure zone - if other specify below
values: Zone B, Zone C, Zone D, Specific Design, Other (specify below)

name: Reason to pass as follows (if applicable):Exposure zones matches zone advised on plans. Refer NZBC/B2 and NZS 3604. Note- "D" zone is sea spray zone (500m from high tide mark of sea or 100m from sheltered tidal estuary- advise customer of additional metal protection and 25 mPa concrete strength requirements.

Reason to pass as follows (if applicable):Check ground soil bearing. Probe natural ground to ensure ground is stiff and firm. If unsure ground does not meet 300kPa minimum or fill and other material present, request geotechnical engineer to confirm and certify.
Geotechnical engineer to certify - pass once relevant documentation is attached
Ground contours and surface water control

Ground contours and shape as per site plan. Surface water overland flow is directed away from building. Surface water catchment or drainage (eg silt traps) may be required to control surface water if it is uncontrolled and could flow into neighbouring properties or under the building. No subfloor surface water flows or ponding potential is checked at this stage. This issue may not have been detailed on plans and will need to be addressed as an amendment or minor variation.

Reason to pass as follows (if applicable):Confirm depth and locations of drains within the build vicinity. Foundation clearance from drains and depth below 45deg line of surcharge inference as per plan. Use manholes to confirm invert depth. Check that there will be sufficient space for future planned services

Refer Code of Practice Inspections for more detailed description. 100dia perforated drain (eg novacoil or draincoil) with geotextile filter sock installed at base of retaining wall. To fall towards outlet. Have ends accessible for future flushing out.
Strip foundation width, depth and layout as per plan
Record strip foundation width x depth (mm)

Foundation layout as per plan- includes returns, extent of partial foundations and base of foundation level and min 450mm deep. Height indicators installed to ensure correct depth achieved when pouring. Height indicators (eg height pegs) installed to ensure correct depth achieved when pouring.
Strip foundation: base level and clean. Sides stable
Steps in strip foundation greater than 600mm require engineer design. Note, there may be a requirement for a control joint in block work above this step and therefore make affect starter positions.
Clean out all foreign debris and loose earth from foundation
Level the base of the foundation
Strip foundation: Max 600mm steps in foundation

Base to be level. No sloping foundation base permitted without specific engineer design. Trench to be clean and clear of rubbish, ground debris and edges stable to avoid collapse during concrete pour.
Step in foundation greater than 600mm. Reduce steps or provide engineer approval
Height indicators installed to ensure correct depth achieved when pouring.
Strip foundations reinforcing size, grade, laps and bends as per plans.

Includes main longitudinal reinforcing, stirrups, links, ties and starters. Check the reinforcing markings and sizes against the plans. Ensure laps min lap lengths are achieved. Ties/ stirrups/links sizes and centres confirmed. All reinforcing needs to be tied and supported to avoid any movement during concrete pour. Reinforcing free of loose rust and mud build up.
Strip foundation: Ties/ stirrups/links size and centres record
Ties/ stirrups/links sizes checked and centres confirmed. Record size and centres. Ensure they are all securely tied to avoid any movement during concrete pour
Strip foundation: Starter sizes and centres
Starter sizes and centres checked and recorded. Starters need to be tied into cage and supported to avoid any movement during concrete pour.
Strip foundation: Reinforcing clean, tied and supported
Reinforcing free of loose rust and mud build up. It needs to be well tied and supported to avoid it moving during the concrete pour.
Ensure 75mm cover to direct ground contact, 50mm against formwork/ air/ DPM and 30mm to top of interior slab.
If specified cover differs from above provide engineers approval
Strip foundation: Reinforcing bar chairs/ spacers installed
Install reinforcing chairs or support to ensure adequate concrete cover is achieved and bars are supported in place during concrete pour
Any material used to support cage cannot provide a direct moisture bridge to reinforcing e.g. using reinforcement bars pushed into the ground to support cage
Strip foundation: Drain bridging as per design
Reason to pass as follows (if applicable): Check that drain bridging design assumptions is correct on-site by checking location/depths of drains and clearance to foundations are as per design.
Strip foundation: DPM installed under foundation

Reason to pass as follows (if applicable): Damp proof membrane (DPM) has been installed to foundations where tanking is required eg basement retaining walls. Tanking to be continuous and all joints sealed. Material as per plan. This item also used to record specific water stop or water bar products installed in foundation eg  Volclay waterstop RX swelling strip (take photo)
Select appropriate pile/post - if other specify below
values: Bored Timber, Concrete, Steel, Specific engineer design, Other (specify below)

name: Piles/post footing sizes and general layout
Layout and shape of building as per plan. Footing sizes checked as per plan.
Ensuring pile layout as per plan (eg number of rows and shape of building)
Check maximum pile centres and maximum spacing between bearer lines as per plan.
450mm deep minimum for ordinary and braced piles, 900mm deep for anchor piles. Braced and anchor pile (1.5kPa floor) minimum 350 square or 400 diameter. Record width and depth

Layout as per plan. Footing and pile sizes checked. Heights, centres, spacings, treatment and grade as per plan. Any pile cut below 300mm above ground level to have DPC between the pile and bearer.  DPC must overlap the past framing by 6mm minimum. Note- minimum height of any pile is 150mm above ground level. Check if final pile heights will still meet bracing requirements eg; piles too high for anchor pile will require bracing change and likewise, piles too low for braces may need to be re-designed as anchor piles. This may trigger amendment or minor variation requirement.
Piles are set in holes plumb and raised off ground at bottom 100mm min
Piles to be set in hole plumb and supported. Punch pad below min 100mm. SED may require deeper punch pads for bigger poles.
Select appropriate pile/post treatment - if other specify below
Check the treatment- H5 required for any piles. Anchor pile timber grade stamps/labels checked.
Strip foundation: Drain bridging as per design
Reason to pass as follows (if applicable): Check that drain bridging design assumptions is correct on-site by checking location/depths of drains and clearance to foundations are as per design.
If "Other" foundation type (attach relevant supporting documentation & evidence here)
Council Inspection completed, attached and any relevant observations closed out
